  "plain_language_assessment": "M5n does not speed up full Flye. It removes a protocol dependency: the CUDA read-alignment chain worker can now produce the same pre-divergence chain DP output as the CPU replay without reading CPU-generated chain-divergence rows. This is the prerequisite for a later Flye-side mode that skips CPU chainReadAlignments for selected reads and then runs CPU divergence filtering on CUDA-produced chains.",
